                        <h4>Experiences gained:</h4>
                        <p>I had several responsibilities to manage since I was in complete control of the show.</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li type="square">Held auditions and callbacks with other the other directors this semester. This process spanned about 20 hours over the course of two days.</li>
                            <li type="square">Set up practice schedule that would work around everyone's free time, and led each practice with a general goal for the night.</li>
                            <li type="square">Managed and oversaw the budget for the production, and carefully used the full $500 we were provided. You can view my budget here.</li>
                            <li type="square">Responsible for designing the set. The audience configuration placed the stage in the corner, and I based the overall set so that it would be convenient for the entire audience.</li>
                            <li type="square">Created the blocking (movement) for the actors, and worked with them to establish the interpretation of their characters.</li>
                            <li type="square">Found a publicist and worked with her to establish a calendar for promoting the show through several different means.</li>
                            <li type="square">Contacted a photographer for publicity photos, and chose locations that fitted the overall feel of the show.</li>
                            <li type="square">Worked at solving conflict between actors, and focused on collaborating a strong performance by bringing different kinds of individuals together as a whole for the show.</li>
                            <li type="square">Designed the overall concept of the poster (seen above), and received photoshop assistance from a fellow student.</li>
                            <li type="square">Worked with the AV department on campus to record the show with three different cameras on a live switcher.</li>
                            <li type="square">Designed all aspects of the sound by building sound effects through different channels, creating old radio broadcasts, and picking pre-show music that matched the theme.</li>
                            <li type="square">Built a dramaturgy that was displayed at the entrance to the theatre.</li>
                            <li type="square">Compiled bios, photos, and wrote the directors note for the performance's program, which can be viewed here.</li>
                        </ul>
                       
